HTML Structure:

Header: Contains the title of the system and a search bar for inputting city names.
Main:
Overview Section: Displays the current weather (temperature, humidity, wind speed, and location).
Map Section: Displays the map using Leaflet.js based on the latitude and longitude of the input city.
CSS Styling:

Simple layout with a green header and styled weather info sections.
The map and weather information are centrally aligned with a responsive design that adjusts for mobile screens.
JavaScript:

Fetches weather data using the OpenWeatherMap API.
Displays the weather data on the page.
Uses Leaflet.js to display a map based on the geographical coordinates of the fetched city.
You can search for any city, and it will display its weather and map.
Notes:
Replace apiKey in the JavaScript code with your OpenWeatherMap API key.
You can extend the system by adding more features like weekly forecasts, air quality data, etc.
This is a clean and simple setup for an environment monitoring system without using any Bootstrap concepts. Let me know if you need more features or improvements!







